    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#smith-porcher1864"/>, n. <citedRange>2</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl>Blass, <ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4839</citedRange></bibl> (fragment A);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XI.48, XII.12</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>35</citedRange>, fig. 33 (fragment A)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XI.57</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl> <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>185</citedRange> (fragment B, 
                        without illustration, with reference to fragment A)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>008900</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                   
                <div type="textpart" subtype="block" n="A">
                   <ab>   
                       <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_ης"><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><unclear>η</unclear>ς</seg></name> 
                           <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64407"><name nymRef="#Ἱπποκλῆς" type="patronymic">Ἱππoκλεῦς</name></persName></persName>
                       <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62538"><name nymRef="#Ἀγασικλῆς">Ἀγασικλῆς</name> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65992"><name nymRef="#Φιλοκλῆς" type="patronymic">Φιλοκλεῦς</name></persName></persName>
                       <lb n="3"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλλωνι</name></persName> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w>
                    </ab>
                </div>
                
                <div type="textpart" subtype="block" n="B">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><space extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Τιμα_"><seg part="I">Τιμ<unclear>α</unclear></seg></name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> 
                        <lb n="2"/><space extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀγα_" type="patronymic"><seg part="I">Ἀγα<choice><unclear>μ</unclear><unclear>ν</unclear><unclear>κ</unclear></choice></seg></name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></persName></persName>
                    </ab>
                 </div>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="A.1"><lem><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/><unclear>η</unclear>ς</lem> 
                    <rdg resp="#SECir"><supplied reason="lost">Τιμασικλῆ</supplied>ς</rdg>
                </app>
                    <app loc="B.1"><lem>Τιμ<unclear>α</unclear><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir">Τιμ<unclear>α</unclear><supplied reason="lost">σικλῆς <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64407"><name>Ἱπποκλεῦς</name></persName></supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="B.2"><lem>Ἀγα<choice><unclear>μ</unclear><unclear>ν</unclear><unclear>κ</unclear></choice>
                                <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62538"><name>Ἀγα<unclear>σ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ικλῆς</supplied></name></persName> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65992"><name><supplied reason="lost">Φιλοκλεῦς</supplied></name></persName></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
                
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>A. <supplied reason="lost">Untel</supplied> fils d'Hippoklès et Agasiklès fils de Philoklès ont consacré à Apollon comme dîme.</p>
                <p>B. Tim<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> fils d'Aga<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>A. <supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied> son of Hippokles and Agasikles son of Philokles dedicated to Apollo as a tithe.</p>
                <p>B. Tim<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> son of Aga<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
                <p>A. <supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> figlio di Hippokles e Agasikles figlio di Philokles hanno dedicato ad Apollo come decima.</p>
                <p>B. Tim<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> figlio di Aga<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Pugliese Carratelli was right in attributing both blocks to the same exedra, but his restorations are not cautious enough.</p>
                <p>At A.1 the space is not sufficient for the 8 letters he supposes.</p>
                <p>B has not the whole formula of dedication, but probably bears on two lines the name and patronym of the person whose statue stood above. 
                    The 4th letter of the patronym is surely no <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σ</foreign>, but might be <foreign xml:lang="grc">Μ, Ν</foreign> or 
                    <foreign xml:lang="grc">Κ</foreign>, rather than <foreign xml:lang="grc">I</foreign>.</p> 
            </div></body>
